#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:2
msgid "How to contribute"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:4
msgid ""
"The Nix ecosystem is developed by many volunteers and a few paid developers, "
"maintaining one of the largest open source software distributions in the "
"world. Keeping it working and up to date – and improving it continuously – "
"would not be possible without your support!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:7
msgid ""
"This guide shows how you can contribute to {term}`Nix`, {term}`Nixpkgs` or "
"{term}`NixOS`. It assumes that you're already somewhat proficient with basic "
"concepts and workflows, which are outlined in the [beginner tutorial series]"
"(tutorials). The most important aspects are [the Nix language](reading-nix-"
"language), the various Nixpkgs mechanisms for [constructing derivations to "
"build software](packaging-tutorial), [the module system](module-system-"
"tutorial), and [NixOS integration tests](integration-testing-vms)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:12
msgid ""
"If you cannot contribute time, consider [donating to the NixOS Foundation on "
"Open Collective](https://opencollective.com/nixos)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:14
msgid ""
"Currently the focus is on [funding in-person events](https://github.com/"
"NixOS/foundation/issues?q=is%3Aissue%20label%3Afunding-request%20) to share "
"knowledge and grow the community of developers proficient with Nix. With "
"enough budget, it would be possible to pay for ongoing maintenance and "
"development of critical infrastructure and code – demanding work that we "
"cannot expect to be done by volunteers indefinitely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:18
msgid "Getting started"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:20
msgid ""
"Start by asking informed questions, after reading [reference documentation]"
"(reference) and the code relevant to what you care about."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:22
msgid ""
"[Join our community communication platforms](https://nixos.org/community) to "
"get in contact with other users and developers. Check out and consider "
"participating in our [community teams](https://nixos.org/community/"
"#governance-teams) if you're interested in a particular topic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:25
msgid ""
"All the source code and documentation is on [GitHub](https://github.com/"
"NixOS), and you need a GitHub account to propose changes. Technical "
"discussions happen in issue and pull request comments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:29
msgid ""
"If you are new to Nix, consider [contributing documentation](./documentation/"
"index.md) first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:31
msgid ""
"This is where we need the most help and where it is the easiest to begin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:33
msgid ""
"Documentation and contribution guides are often incomplete or outdated, much "
"as we would like them to be otherwise. We're working on it. You can help and "
"improve the situation for everyone by immediately solving problems with the "
"contribution workflow as you encounter them. This may slow you down with "
"addressing your original concern. But it will make it a lot easier for "
"anyone to make meaningful contributions in the future. And it will lead to "
"better code and documentation in the long run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:41
msgid "Report an issue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:44
msgid ""
"For asking general questions about the code or how to do things, please use "
"our [community communication platforms](https://nixos.org/community)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:46
msgid ""
"To state technical problems and propose solutions, open GitHub issues and "
"close them when the problem is resolved or invalidated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:49
msgid ""
"We can only fix issues that we know of, so please report any issue you "
"encounter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:51
msgid ""
"Report issues with {term}`Nix` (including the [Nix reference manual](https://"
"nix.dev/manual/nix/stable)) at <https://github.com/NixOS/nix/issues>."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:53
msgid ""
"Report issues with {term}`Nixpkgs` or {term}`NixOS` (including packages, "
"configuration modules, the [Nixpkgs manual](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/"
"stable), and the [NixOS manual](https://nixos.org/manual/nixos/stable)) at "
"<https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/issues>."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:55
msgid ""
"Make sure that there is not already an open issue for your problem. Please "
"follow the issue template and fill in all requested information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:58
msgid ""
"Take particular care to provide a minimal, easy-to-understand example to "
"reproduce the problem you are facing. You should also show what you have "
"found in attempts to solve the problem yourself. This makes it much more "
"likely for the issue to be resolved eventually, and is important for "
"multiple reasons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:62
msgid "A reproducible sample is concise and unambiguous."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:64
msgid ""
"This helps with triaging issues, understanding the problem, finding the root "
"cause, and developing a solution. Your preliminary research further helps "
"maintainers with analysis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:67
msgid "It allows anyone to determine if the issue is still relevant."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:69
msgid ""
"Issues can remain unaddressed for a long time. Deciding what to do with "
"them, even after months or years have passed, requires checking if the "
"underlying problem persists or was resolved. This has to be easy to do: then "
"anyone can help out with triaging, and notify maintainers to close or re-"
"prioritise issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:73
msgid "The sample can be used for a regression test when solving the problem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:76
msgid ""
"Ideally you would also propose or sketch a solution. The perfect issue is, "
"in fact, a pull request that solves the problem directly and ensures with "
"tests that it cannot occur again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:81
msgid ""
"Please open issues to request new features (such as packages, modules, "
"commands, ...) only if you are willing and able to implement them yourself. "
"Then the issue can be used to gauge user interest, to determine if the "
"feature fits into the project, and to discuss implementation strategies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:85
msgid "Contribute to Nix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:87
msgid ""
"{term}`Nix` is the cornerstone of the ecosystem, and is mostly written in C+"
"+."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:89
msgid ""
"If you want to help with development, check the [contributing guide in the "
"Nix repository on GitHub](https://github.com/NixOS/nix/blob/master/"
"CONTRIBUTING.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:92
msgid "Contribute to Nixpkgs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:95
msgid ""
"For a verbal introduction, watch the NixCon 2024 talk [Becoming a Nixpkgs "
"Contributor](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eijTOBBbCv4)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:98
msgid ""
"{term}`Nixpkgs` is a large software project with various areas of "
"development. You can find inspiration for things to improve in the [Nixpkgs "
"issue tracker][nixpkgs issues]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:103
msgid ""
"If you want to help, start with the [contributing guide in the Nixpkgs "
"repository on GitHub](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/"
"CONTRIBUTING.md) to get an overview of the code and the contribution "
"process. There are also [programming-language-specific instructions](https://"
"nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/unstable/#chap-language-support) for adding "
"packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:106
msgid "Contribute to NixOS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:108
msgid ""
"{term}`NixOS` is a collectively developed Linux distribution that can be "
"configured conveniently in a highly flexible way through declarative "
"programming interfaces. The code for modules and default configurations is "
"in the [`nixos` directory of the `nixpkgs` GitHub repository](https://github."
"com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tree/master/nixos)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:111
msgid ""
"See the [NixOS manual's development section](https://nixos.org/manual/nixos/"
"stable/index.html#ch-development) to get started with making improvements. "
"Contributor documentation specific to NixOS is still lacking, but most "
"conventions for [Nixpkgs contributions](contribute-nixpkgs) apply. Help with "
"improving that is greatly appreciated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:115
msgid ""
"Check [issues labeled `good-first-bug`](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/"
"issues?q=is%3Aopen+label%3A%223.skill%3A+good-first-bug%22+label%3A%226."
"topic%3A+nixos%22) if you're a new contributor. If you know your way around, "
"working on [popular issues][nixos issues] will be highly appreciated by "
"other NixOS users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:120
msgid "How to get help"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-contribute.md:122
msgid ""
"If you prepared a pull request and need help moving forward, check "
"[contributing-how-to-get-help](https://nix.dev/contributing/how-to-get-"
"help#contributing-how-to-get-help) for more information."
msgstr ""
